Cell["\<\
A multiplication factor of 1/2 should correspond to each pair of equivalent \
propagators, i.e. starting at the same interaction vertex and ending at the \
same vertex. Additionally, a factor of 1/2 appears whenever an anomalous \
propagator is contracted to the same interaction vertex (anomalous loop). In \
these diagrams, no equivalent lines are present in the graphs. Also, \
anomalous loops do not occur. BogAntidiagarison with the input values in the \
array \[OpenCurlyQuote]GGFMult\[CloseCurlyQuote] is done, for the purpose of \
checking the initial data.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.888317144112847*^9, 3.888317221803842*^9}, {
   3.8883172536792126`*^9, 3.8883172834136724`*^9}, {3.8884104851279383`*^9, 
